cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with power allocation in multi-cell OFDMA networks, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses a pricing mechanism to determine the throughput contribution of each base station, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper formulates a biobjective problem and proposes an algorithm to achieve the solutions on the boundary of the efficient set, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses the term "throughput contribution" as a performance metric, which is related to multimedia. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses the method of Pascoletti and Serafini scalarization, which is related to game theory.
